{
  "answer": "Arthur Young's *Travels during the years 1787, 1788 and 1789* is cited as eyewitness testimony to deforestation in the Pyrenees forests (near Bagnères de Luchon, with men cutting young birches for barrel hoops) in Charles Comte's *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, chapter 13 (\"Influence du déboisement des montagnes sur les fleuves et les rivières\").[^1]\n\nThe Lartigues passage reads: \"...This beautiful and noble forest of Lartigues has experienced a devastation so general, that it is almost entirely destroyed; there are no young shoots to replace the trees that have disappeared, and, in ten or twelve years, it will be nothing more than a bare mountain, with some miserable shrubs browsed by goats or by other animals.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: Charles Comte, *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, ch. 13, [p-4ce3c5](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-la-propriete-vol-i-2c7a99/13-influence-du-deboisement-des-montagnes-sur-les-fle/translation/#p-4ce3c5).\n[^2]: Charles Comte, *Traité de la propriété: VOL I*, ch. 13, [p-5e30bb](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-la-propriete-vol-i-2c7a99/13-influence-du-deboisement-des-montagnes-sur-les-fle/translation/#p-5e30bb).",
